The article discusses the historical relationship between the United States and France, highlighting the shared values and common interests between the two countries. It mentions the upcoming state visit of French President Emmanuel Macron and his wife Brigitte Macron to the United States, which marks the first official state visit under the Trump administration. The article also emphasizes the historical significance of the visit, tracing the relationship between France and the United States back to the American Revolutionary War and the support provided by France to the American colonists. It further mentions the strong trade relationship between the two countries and their participation in various international organizations. Overall, the article emphasizes the importance of the enduring bond between the United States and France.